  "prompt": "What are the reasons why people hate electric cars?",
  "response": "Here are some common reasons why people are skeptical or critical of electric cars:\n\n1. Initial Cost\n- Higher upfront purchase price\n- More expensive than comparable gas vehicles\n\n2. Range Limitations\n- Shorter driving range compared to gas vehicles\n- Concerns about long-distance travel\n- \"Range anxiety\"\n\n3. Charging Infrastructure\n- Limited charging stations\n- Long charging times\n- Inconvenience of charging compared to quick gas refueling\n\n4. Battery Concerns\n- Potential battery replacement costs\n- Environmental impact of battery production\n- Battery performance in extreme temperatures\n\n5. Performance Perceptions\n- Concerns about acceleration and power\n- Less familiar driving experience\n- Perceived as less exciting than traditional cars\n\n6. Environmental Debates\n- Electricity generation's carbon footprint\n- Battery manufacturing emissions\n- Questions about overall environmental benefits\n\n7. Cultural and Emotional Factors\n- Attachment to traditional combustion engines\n- Resistance to technological change\n- Perceived loss of automotive \"character\"\n\n8. Practical Limitations\n- Less suitable for rural areas\n- Challenges in cold climates\n- Limited model variety\n\n9. Potential Hidden Costs\n- Potential electrical grid strain\n- Home charging equipment expenses\n- Potential electricity rate increases\n\nThese reasons reflect various economic, technological, and psychological barriers to electric vehicle adoption.",
